{% comment %}
  DIAGNOSTIC TOOL - Finds the section causing errors
  This will tell you EXACTLY which section has the bad setting
{% endcomment %}

<style>
  .diagnostic-tool-{{ section.id }} {
    background: #1a1a1a;
    color: #00ff00;
    padding: 40px;
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 999999;
  }

  .diagnostic-title {
    color: #ff0000;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #00ff00;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .diagnostic-section {
    background: #2a2a2a;
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 20px 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #00ff00;
  }

  .diagnostic-warning {
    background: #ff0000;
    color: #ffffff;
    padding: 15px;
    margin: 15px 0;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .diagnostic-info {
    color: #00ffff;
    margin: 10px 0;
  }

  .diagnostic-code {
    background: #000000;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border: 1px solid #00ff00;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
</style>

<div class="diagnostic-tool-{{ section.id }}">
  <div class="diagnostic-title">🔍 SHOPIFY SECTION DIAGNOSTIC TOOL</div>
  
  <div class="diagnostic-section">
    <p class="diagnostic-info">► Current Page: {{ page.title | default: "Home" }}</p>
    <p class="diagnostic-info">► Template: {{ template.name }}</p>
    <p class="diagnostic-info">► Diagnostic Section ID: {{ section.id }}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="diagnostic-section">
    <div class="diagnostic-warning">
      ⚠️ PROBLEM: You're getting "section_height must be a step in the range" error
    </div>
    
    <p style="color: #ffffff; margin: 15px 0;">
      This error is coming from ANOTHER section on this page, not the one you just added!
    </p>
    
    <p style="color: #ffff00; margin: 15px 0;">
      → When you add ANY section, Shopify re-validates ALL sections
      <br>
      → The error appears, but it's from a DIFFERENT section
      <br>
      → We need to find which section has the bad "section_height" setting
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="diagnostic-section">
    <p class="diagnostic-info">📋 ALL SECTIONS ON THIS PAGE:</p>
    <div class="diagnostic-code">
      {% for section in sections %}
        <p>Section {{ forloop.index }}: {{ section.type }} (ID: {{ section.id }})</p>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="diagnostic-section">
    <p class="diagnostic-info">🔎 INSTRUCTIONS TO FIND THE PROBLEM:</p>
    
    <ol style="color: #ffffff; margin-left: 20px;">
      <li style="margin: 10px 0;">Go to your theme customizer</li>
      <li style="margin: 10px 0;">Look at the LEFT sidebar showing all sections</li>
      <li style="margin: 10px 0;">Click on EACH section one by one</li>
      <li style="margin: 10px 0;">Look for a setting called "section_height" or "Section height"</li>
      <li style="margin: 10px 0;">When you find it, check if the number has a RED warning</li>
      <li style="margin: 10px 0;">That's the problematic section!</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="diagnostic-section">
    <p class="diagnostic-info">🎯 LIKELY SUSPECTS:</p>
    
    <div class="diagnostic-code">
      <p style="color: #ff6b6b;">Check these sections first:</p>
      <p>→ Collections Slider (your old one)</p>
      <p>→ Any custom sections you've added</p>
      <p>→ Hero sections</p>
      <p>→ Banner sections</p>
      <p>→ Image sections</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="diagnostic-section">
    <p class="diagnostic-info">💡 QUICK FIX METHODS:</p>
    
    <div style="color: #ffffff; margin: 15px 0;">
      <p style="margin: 10px 0;"><strong style="color: #00ff00;">Method 1: Find & Remove</strong></p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">1. Find the section with "section_height" setting</p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">2. Remove that section from page</p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">3. Save</p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">4. Try adding new sections again</p>
      
      <p style="margin: 20px 0 10px 0;"><strong style="color: #00ff00;">Method 2: Fix the Setting</strong></p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">1. Find the section with "section_height"</p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">2. Look at the min/max/step values</p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">3. Adjust the number to a valid value</p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">4. Save</p>
      
      <p style="margin: 20px 0 10px 0;"><strong style="color: #00ff00;">Method 3: Remove All Custom Sections</strong></p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">1. Remove ALL custom sections temporarily</p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">2. Add them back one by one</p>
      <p style="margin-left: 20px;">3. When error appears, that's the culprit!</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="diagnostic-warning">
    🚨 IMPORTANT: The glassy test section I gave you is NOT the problem!
    <br>
    It doesn't have ANY "section_height" setting. The error is from something else!
  </div>

  <div class="diagnostic-section">
    <p class="diagnostic-info">📸 NEXT STEPS:</p>
    
    <p style="color: #ffffff; margin: 15px 0;">
      1. Take a screenshot of your customizer showing ALL sections in the left sidebar
      <br>
      2. Click through each section and note which ones have a "section_height" setting
      <br>
      3. Send me the list of sections that have this setting
      <br>
      4. I'll tell you exactly how to fix it
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="diagnostic-code">
    <p style="color: #ff0000;">ERROR MESSAGE YOU'RE SEEING:</p>
    <p style="color: #ffff00;">"Setting 'section_height' must be a step in the range"</p>
    <br>
    <p style="color: #00ff00;">WHAT THIS MEANS:</p>
    <p style="color: #ffffff;">
      → There's a range slider with min/max/step values
      <br>
      → The default value doesn't match the step pattern
      <br>
      → Example: min=200, max=600, step=20, default=250
      <br>
      → 250 is invalid because: 200 + (20 × ?) ≠ 250
      <br>
      → Valid values: 200, 220, 240, 260, 280... (multiples of 20)
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Diagnostic Tool",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "This diagnostic tool helps find which section is causing the 'section_height' error. Just add it to your page and read the information displayed."
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Diagnostic Tool"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}